      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/10/5068",
      "text": [
        ": سَأَلْتُهُ عَنْ رَجُلٍ يَفْتَرِي عَلَى رَجُلٍ مِنْ جَاهِلِيَّةِ اَلْعَرَبِ قَالَ \"يُضْرَبُ حَدّاً\" قُلْتُ يُضْرَبُ حَدّاً قَالَ \"نَعَمْ إِنَّ ذَلِكَ يَدْخُلُ عَلَى رَسُولِ اَللَّهِ صَلَّى اَللَّهُ عَلَيْهِ وَ آلِهِ \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5068 - It was narrated from Safwan from Abu Bakr Al-Hadrami from Abu Abdullah (as) who said: I asked Imam (as) about a man who slanders a man from the pre-Islamic Arabs.\nImam (as) said: \"He is to be given the legal punishment.\"\nI asked: \"Is he to be given the legal punishment?\"\nHe said: \"Yes, because that offense reaches the Messenger of Allah (swt) (peace be upon him and his family).\""
        ]
      }
    },
